headline: NASH Industries Unveils its First Series of 'Make in India' Motherboards Powered by Intel's Raptor Lake Platform
summary: NASH Industries recently announced the successful launch of its first series of 'Make in India' motherboards, designed and developed using the Intel B760 chipset for Intel's Raptor Lake (RPL) processor family. This milestone marks a significant step forward in India's journey toward indigenous electronics design and manufacturing excellence.
